{"word":"μαυρόω","slug":"μαυρόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μαυρόω</b></el> <el>(μαυρόω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>for <a href='S:ἀμαυρόω'><el>ἀμαυρόω</el></a>, metri gratia,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to darken, to blind, make powerless</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to make dim</i> or <i>obscure</i>, or <i>forgotten</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become dim</i> or <i>obscure</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}